⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Paper
node AHX · AHX · ⟦The Paper:AHX:f59c19⟧

WHO   — The Paper — 'American History X'
WHAT  — The reckoning as writing: a boy made to put his brother's hate and reform into words, the act of understanding the film performs.
WHERE — AHX · American History X (1998)  Framework inputs: American History X (1998, dir. Tony Kaye, New Line); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film is, structurally, the paper — the title is the assignment, and the narration is the writing of it.
HOW   — By turning the assignment into the film's spine: to understand the hate, you have to write it down honestly.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the assignment that names the film. To get past the hate, the boy had to write it down — and he just barely finished me.

